        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the best SEO tool for a small business in 2026?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For most small businesses, theStacc at $99/mo (or $167/mo bundled with GBP + social) — because it does the work instead of giving you a dashboard to read. For the free baseline, every small business should set up Google Search Console and Google Business Profile. For budget keyword research, Ubersuggest or Mangools. For DIY local SEO, BrightLocal or Localo.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can a small business really do SEO without an agency?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes — most small businesses over-pay for agencies that produce 4 articles a month and a PDF report. A $99/mo theStacc subscription publishes 30 articles, a free Google Business Profile drives local pack visibility, and a $39/mo BrightLocal account tracks the impact. Hire an agency for strategy or competitive verticals, not for execution that tools handle.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How much should a small business spend on SEO tools?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Most small businesses get 80% of the result with a $99–$200/mo budget. Free baseline: Google Search Console + Google Business Profile + Yoast SEO. Add theStacc at $99/mo for content + on-page automation. Add BrightLocal at $39/mo or Localo at $29/mo if local matters. That stack outperforms most $1,500/mo agency retainers.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the most important SEO tool to start with?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google Search Console — it is free, official, and the single most important tool to start with. It shows which queries already bring traffic, where you rank, what is indexed, and what is broken. Every other SEO tool is interpreting data Search Console gives you for free.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do small businesses still need content if Google has AI Overviews?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes — AI Overviews are sourced from indexed, well-structured content. The businesses cited in AI Overviews are the ones that publish helpful articles, structure them with FAQs and schema, and earn brand mentions. Skipping content because of AI Overviews is the fastest way to disappear from both classic SERPs and AI surfaces.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is theStacc better than hiring a freelance writer?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For most small businesses, yes — by a wide margin. A freelance writer charges $80–$250 per article. theStacc publishes 30 articles a month for $99 (≈$3.30 each), auto-optimised and auto-published. Freelance writers still win for opinion pieces, podcasts, and founder thought leadership — but for recurring SEO content, theStacc is the better unit economics.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What's the difference between free SEO tools and paid ones?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Free tools (Search Console, GBP, Yoast) cover diagnostics and basics. Paid tools cover three things free tools don't — competitor data, content optimisation at scale, and done-for-you publishing. The smartest small-business stack is free tools for measurement, theStacc for production, and one budget paid tool (SE Ranking, Ubersuggest, Mangools) for keyword research.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

